REASON: THE HANDLE WILL IMPACT THE ARM ON THE 'ISC RISER MOUNT'. THE 'LPM-1H' OPTIC MOUNT IS RECOMMENDED FOR RIFLES WITH LEFT-SIDE CHARGING HANDLES. The ISC Riser optic mount is manufactured from high quality aluminum alloy and has been hardcoat anodized for added surface strength, abrasion resistance, and corrosion protection. ISC is an abbreviation for 'Iron Sight Capable' as this mount allows use of irons sights when attached to the side rail.The picatinny rail is centered over the receiver cover and is positioned away from ejected shell casings. This mount should only be used with optics that will not extend into the path of ejected casings - such as red dot optics. If an optic is used that extends beyond the picatinny rail, there is a high probability that the optic will be impacted regularly by ejected casings.Additional details:- attaches to the rifle using the CSA side rail (side rails can be purchased in the 'Parts and Accessories' section). AUSTRIAN Keiser A Vienne Antique Percussion Pistol
Long Belt Pistol w Olry A Nancy Marked Lock
Here we present an antique George Keiser A Vienne Percussion Pistol, made circa 1840 in Vienna, Austria. This pistol was made for putting large holes in things. It could be carried on the belt or on the saddle. It was equally suited for combat as it was for target shooting as it does have both front and rear sights, not a given during this period in firearms history. The lock is marked “OLRY A NANCY”.
